 stack that does not tie up cpu_resources with its 1 hour (3600,000)</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_6_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="eFbm(=^RN,,#Md8v.e`-"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="8.7uE*#k$)YViU@Us`5`"><field name="TEXT">Also the 'if(false)' mini-stacks will be skipped by cpu, for further non-resource burdening</field></shadow></value><next><block type="controls_if" id="0E0e:Up^*}=0Ow4}G;-O"><value name="IF0"><shadow type="logic_boolean" id="*4fnE7rpkmVDGwsWxLcL"><field name="BOOL">FALSE</field></shadow></value><statement name="DO0"><block type="quest_Note_6_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Big_Func" id="uR(}S%V8|mApo1Xh.^ZR"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="!a@}AkhT=^-j!)bFgj+~"><field name="TEXT">Staff: Very Important Notes</field></shadow></value><next><block type="controls_if" id="2[F+OSv~IZ}!Ek;@xh@2"><value name="IF0"><shadow type="logic_boolean" id="P.5-Yl?p?*h,eg@F(+%/"><field name="BOOL">FALSE</field></shadow></value><statement name="DO0"><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="RAS{_s~H9TLU+X$Sw?7_"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="EO900Vb4v[+2n)Tk$c:T"><field name="TEXT">Levels 1, 2, 2.1</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="kS!SnA7ai0{W{g*Mdt7."><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="?{:2/@{cN3gy2/w{y7Ja"><field name="TEXT">* Level 1: Hardcoded Static via Actual_Numbers for MotorPower%</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="gyGy),QEmBbSh,!#lY#;"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="PlpI1Zc2^/36]H{=K85U"><field name="TEXT">* Level 2: Softcoded Dynamic via Variables/Constants for MotorPower% </field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="hzlp!=WspCJz=Q*Z|M[Z"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="tkX@ZMoT;]^B/@#?6z6+"><field name="TEXT">* Level 2.1 Add Controller_Joystick * Level 2.2 Add Gear 3 (90%?)</field></shadow></value></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></statement><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="+GfFesUVI4OB!hKZk;Rr"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id=".CAf)5Wd/dw6?Wl0#$s/"><field name="TEXT">Basic Comment_Colors Usage:: Black: Very Big Picture, Blue: Big Picture, Green: Following Block_Code Moddable, Orange: Question/TODO, Magenta: Special Multi-Purpose </field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="V2qb)DmTarWa[BN!./jk"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="qc;E8N0:d1cn3ldARZhi"><field name="TEXT">micro:bit Ver2 Warning during Download is Ignorable Yet Courteously Helpful</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="TeZ7J*hxnwr:.LAYIZ^p"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="X!5Z5Uf$*itq1|$!5L84"><field name="TEXT">'if_then' mini-stacks useful for modular 3-D code select/duplicate/move/delete</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="G/*K^{6[B`,e9jq}0a|j"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="/,4cCu1Fbu1UgJsaU1lc"><field name="TEXT">Light_Gray Functions non-editable (backend staff-use code only)</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="u:9RyzZlc.I)U*VD[voT"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="sv_VjSh5=emvi+cYJJ+T"><field name="TEXT">For Group_CHannel_# (Bot_Id): Propose: 1-10 Staff Use, 11-99 Student Use</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="v*r3dPgvD)tLNqlb)b.A"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="K$N$UM(z(GRO51w0pI35"><field name="TEXT">SW Reset: Long_Press Logo for 3 sec min</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="K)/thSL3n4eJ(RLGTdx*"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="kQF)rAAdWy$oFnDo]9:0"><field name="TEXT">Built-in Diagnostic Test: Short_Press Logo for 1 sec max</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="{eBpprEPzuW+OZOpD)T5"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="*M3nmhsALcK=RpQY^mSa"><field name="TEXT">'Blocks' Window homes 'on start'_stack as top_left corner of editor_screen, until 'on start' is moved below, then next stack to right presides</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_3_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="hc-1^ly~125TMX!TME7G"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="P!68G|UN49{[O;o]9At@"><field name="TEXT">All These Levels are Intermediate Level Coding due to Networking Pairing Involved.  Basic Diagnostic Servo_Motors (Autonomoous) is Beginner Level.</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_3_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="1D_]?6+{oUYW7,0,Ftkj"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="D1xfiuC{o==$Rulu_~rL"><field name="TEXT">This Intermediate Level Network_Pairing has 1sec_Lag Response Time; The Other Advanced Level Network_Pairing has Real_Time Response Time.</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_3_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="Bq6CT2BZ+y}U)B-:1f)H"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="X]lIPr_njk^8?[u*,7;d"><field name="TEXT">For Level 1, can keep 'Forward: set manual_servo_motors' Block functional, yet reset to 0 all other 'set manual_servo_motors' Blocks for Discovery Learning</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_3_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="+Sw!=sox0H-eu?ZK4FUb"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="jL/d9dO,4U%y+eZ[`{88"><field name="TEXT">If duplicate stacks exist, then the highest stack is active and others are non_active</field></shadow></value></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></statement><next><block type="controls_if" id="E.::Kv%_piVUpJ[iPdkn"><value name="IF0"><shadow type="logic_boolean" id="g8e*3qFY/NpAKP5leD|@"><field name="BOOL">FALSE</field></shadow></value><statement name="DO0"><block type="quest_Note_6_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Big_Func" id="{3jns#h!?#O.POdhpkr^"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="u}:SIG9:$[m_gjc5D)+p"><field name="TEXT">Staff: Important Notes</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="o=R?`mJL-Yj]Ls~wN:Go"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="3o69)0#t~t|W2e1eLWyQ"><field name="TEXT">Upon open file, Editor zooms in on closest stack to right of original_origin from project_creation</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="n@1U4WhVMQ`Uk#3gg|d#"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="@C-Px30pE4Tg8:}-]@l["><field name="TEXT">Semantic Naming prefers '_' vs. '-' since latter can be conufused with minus_sign</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="]`Bp01*_{`$:UMt.vWef"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="Sp)^$?FnX}Zc0i$M%4Mh"><field name="TEXT">'every 360000 ms' (1 hour) Stacks can be ignored, esp w/ 'if false' embedded</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="1A2@CC^ZRea2qrPA;*+A"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="`.6K$(y-ynwTpy0t6GrO"><field name="TEXT">Avoid using 'show leds' Block since will cause lag &amp; degrade real-time response</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="^(s5xKUJ?*dZ}zifsZ_,"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="S7FG+b}x^NIcke(gC/aS"><field name="TEXT">Seems like 'signficant' changes to JavaScript can activate 'format code', rearrange stacks to original position</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="Qm%mWCi|Vt({Q)uVlKH6"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="xfy4OK:9?p?n$K)Q:o+W"><field name="TEXT">Important 'system' variables are 1) _system_Hw_DeviceType__* (Hw=Hardware) and 2) _system_Sw_ModeState__* (Sw=Software)</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="3WGIAI-a7@z`KXW):-[b"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="d=JAiN7%qLBL4eA-=lEh"><field name="TEXT">If Buttons C-F for Gears/Misc, Maybe 'Logo Up/Down' for 'Servo_Arm Up/Down'</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="~!,%Bq^FKyi;u@VAOPBZ"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="dc2fR$nX:y9i${=+U*K9"><field name="TEXT">'Rotatedisplay' could be used on Bot's Led_Screen, but causes light flickering on bottom row, so maybe avoid</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="2o|,^MU{;BeEg*fikxN|"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="hxwl+1[,NsC[,P7%AFef"><field name="TEXT">Reliable/Faster Response If Screen_Led_Graphics After Important Action Blocks Above</field></shadow></value><next><block type="controls_if" id="=KCEA{f/TK$BnZPM+m}8"><value name="IF0"><shadow type="logic_boolean" id="7]y5/iV3vcTB)Sff(!V3"><field name="BOOL">FALSE</field></shadow></value><statement name="DO0"><block type="quest_Note_3_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="b/N|1YJg-ru|Xwu^Gu!y"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="hQNx0w%6rFV[FLjA3T(h"><field name="TEXT">Main upgrade from Lv1 to Lv2 is replacing cpu_laggy 'show leds' block with cpu_fast 'plox x _ y _' block, such as below: </field></shadow></value><next><block type="controls_if" id="^:?*7s0Do:61a:N_W~6$"><mutation elseif="4" else="1"></mutation><value name="IF0"><shadow type="logic_boolean" id="8`!G0Yd/.qp=(Jsfdu3w"><field name="BOOL">FALSE</field></sh